(469, 1, '2018-12-01 04:55:08', '2018-12-01 04:55:08', '<p>The Motlanthe Commission has concluded its public hearings and is now retreating to analyse evidence brought before it.</p><p>Its 3-month deadline to release its findings expires on December 15.</p><p>They released the following statement.</p><p>PRESS STATEMENT</p><p>THE Commission of Inquiry into the Post Election Violence which occurred in Harare on August 1 this year, today concluded its process of gathering oral evidence through public hearings.</p>		\n										<img width=\"790\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-1024x122.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-1024x122.png 1024w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-300x36.png 300w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-768x91.png 768w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-600x71.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 790px) 100vw, 790px\" />											\n		<p>Testimonies, most of which were broadcasted live on ZBC television and Social Media platform were heard from different individuals and organizations in Harare, Bulawayo, Gweru and Mutare</p><p>The Commission was also handed over written evidence as well as audio and video materials including some which were provided by international broadcasters following an appeal made through the Ministry of information, Media and Broadcasting Services.</p><p>The Commission is now collating and analysing all information gathered and has already started compiling its final report and recommendations to be presented to His Excellency President Emrnerson Dambudzo Mnangagwa .</p><p>Headed by former South African President Kgalema Motlanthe the Commission is working day and night in order to present its report way ahead of its 90 day deadline which commenced on 19 September 2018 when the seven member group of local and international eminent parsons was sworn in at State House in Harare.</p>', 'Commission of Enquiry on Harare shooting comes to an end', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '393-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-01 04:55:08', '2018-12-01 04:55:08', '', 393, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/index.php/2018/12/01/393-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(470, 1, '2018-12-01 04:56:53', '2018-12-01 04:56:53', '<p>The Motlanthe Commission has concluded its public hearings and is now retreating to analyse evidence brought before it.</p><p>Its 3-month deadline to release its findings expires on December 15.</p><p>They released the following statement.</p><p>PRESS STATEMENT</p><p>THE Commission of Inquiry into the Post Election Violence which occurred in Harare on August 1 this year, today concluded its process of gathering oral evidence through public hearings.</p>		\n										<img width=\"790\" height=\"94\" src=\"http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-1024x122.png\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-1024x122.png 1024w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-300x36.png 300w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-768x91.png 768w, http://www.zimskynews.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Screen-Shot-2018-11-26-at-11.06.20-600x71.png 600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 790px) 100vw, 790px\" />											\n		<p>Testimonies, most of which were broadcasted live on ZBC television and Social Media platform were heard from different individuals and organizations in Harare, Bulawayo, Gweru and Mutare</p><p>The Commission was also handed over written evidence as well as audio and video materials including some which were provided by international broadcasters following an appeal made through the Ministry of information, Media and Broadcasting Services.</p><p>The Commission is now collating and analysing all information gathered and has already started compiling its final report and recommendations to be presented to His Excellency President Emrnerson Dambudzo Mnangagwa .</p><p>Headed by former South African President Kgalema Motlanthe the Commission is working day and night in order to present its report way ahead of its 90 day deadline which commenced on 19 September 2018 when the seven member group of local and international eminent parsons was sworn in at State House in Harare.</p>', 'Commission of Enquiry on Harare shooting comes to an end', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '393-revision-v1', '', '', '2018-12-01 04:56:53', '2018-12-01 04:56:53', '', 393, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/index.php/2018/12/01/393-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
