(599, 2, '2019-02-12 09:31:57', '2019-02-12 09:31:57', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The late Zimbabwean Music Icon Dr Oliver Mtukudzi was Sunday night remember by the Recording Academy for his contribution in the music industry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The legendary musician died on 23 January 2019 at the age of 66.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He was remembered amongst a host of other artists and industry professionals the music community lost in 20182019.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Recording Academy salutes each individual for their respective talents and contributions to our culture and community.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The 61st GRAMMY Awards telecast on CBS will feature an In Memoriam segment highlighting some of these individuals via a video tribute, and all of these individuals who died prior to Jan. 8, 2019 are included in the official 61st GRAMMY Awards program book.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> Zimbuzz</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Grammy Awards honours Tuku', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'grammy-awards-honours-tuku', '', '', '2019-02-12 09:31:57', '2019-02-12 09:31:57', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=599', 0, 'post', '', 0),
