(605, 2, '2019-02-12 09:48:17', '2019-02-12 09:48:17', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A suspected protestor nabbed for robbery, who initially testified to the court that he was given army uniform at the Zanu PF headquarters, yesterday flipped the script and accused the police officers who arrested him of forcing him to wear a friends military gear.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure><iframe width=\"680\" height=\"170\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shepard Magorimbo&nbsp;told the court that he was arrested in the city centre and was taken to his place of residence by police officers who forced him to wear one Fungai Makonis army fatigue that was in his room.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magorimbo said the only link to the robbery charge he was facing was the mobile number used to transfer money from the complainant.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure><iframe width=\"468\" height=\"60\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>With the state opposing the accuseds bail, considering him a flight risk, Magorimbos lawyer Blessing Mupwanyiwa told the court that the State must have brought the arresting officer to testify if it was opposing bail.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The state however said Magorimbo was in fact arrested by citizens whilst wearing army fatigues.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Magorimbo is facing two counts of robbery.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"350\" src=\"https://duta.in/iHarare-iframe.php\"></iframe></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Advertisements</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:html -->\n<figure><iframe width=\"300\" height=\"250\"></iframe></figure>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>REPORT THIS AD</p>\n<!-- /w