(619, 2, '2019-02-13 12:18:31', '2019-02-13 12:18:31', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MDC Alliance president Nelson Chamisa has said that in the history of nations, the oppressed have always fought the oppressors and they will ultimately prevail even if they are faced with weapons and brute force.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Writing on Twitter, Chamisa said: In the history of nations and struggles of men against men, oppressors have always been fought by the oppressed.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The oppressors have always, out of weakness and desperation, used weapons and brute force to suppress the oppresseds liberation effort. The oppressed ultimately prevail.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chamisa also commended his partys national organizing secretary Amos Chibaya who spent more than two weeks in a Midlands Prison over violent protests in January.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Said Chamisa: Hon Amos Chibaya in high spirit after being released from prison. Hon Chibaya is a peacemaker and hard-worker.The comrade has been targeted because of his indomitability in the fight for democracy and freedom in Zimbabwe.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chamisa has consistently claimed that he won last years presidential election but was denied victory by the Zimbabwe Electoral Commission (ZEC).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chamisa has consistently refused to recognise the incumbent President Emmerson Mnangagwa, branding him illegitimate.  Pindula/<strong><a href=\"https://zoomzimbabwe.com/\">ZOOMZimbabwe</a></strong><ins><br>\n\n</ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'We Will Prevail: Nelson Chamisa', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'we-will-prevail-nelson-chamisa', '', '', '2019-02-13 12:18:31', '2019-02-13 12:18:31', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=619', 0, 'post', '', 0),
