(625, 2, '2019-02-13 12:35:04', '2019-02-13 12:35:04', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>THE ZANU-PF Chegutu West Member of the House of Assembly Dexter Nduna has apologised for what he said in Parliament during a heated argument with independent Norton Member of Parliament Temba Mliswa.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During this weeks Monday heated debate in Parliament,&nbsp;Nduna threatened Mliswa with death and boasted that he had killed countless numbers of people some of whom he did not even know.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nduna has now said he did not mean what he said but spoke in a fit of rage.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He claimed that because it was a fight and therefore, there is no formula to conduct a fight.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the dismissal of Mliswas sister, Mary, from her role as Mashonaland West provincial treasurer, Nduna said she was demoted because of her links with the former G40 cabal.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He cited some of the G40 elements who were in good books with Mary, likes of&nbsp;Shadrack Mashayamombe, Reuben Marumahoko and Saviour Kasukuwere.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mary was also accused of being a proxy for Temba Mliswa in controlling the province.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nduna claimed that Mliswa had control over the whole of the ZANU PF Mashonaland West province through his sister.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He further claimed that the fight in Parliament resulted from Mliswas anger that his sister had been flushed out of ZANU PF. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Dexter Nduna apologises', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'dexter-nduna-apologises', '', '', '2019-02-13 12:35:04', '2019-02-13 12:35:04', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=625', 0, 'post', '', 0),
