(640, 2, '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>It is Valentines Day today and lovers worldwide will be showing each other love and affection through heart-adorned cards, bumper boxes of chocolate, bouquets of red roses and teddy bears.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sadly for the Chicken Inn couple  Makhosana Makho Mguni and Belinda Nyoni, they will not be together on this day of love because of distance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho, who celebrated his 28th birthday yesterday, works in South Africa while his fiance Belinda works at a clothing boutique in Bulawayo.<a href=\"https://nehandaradio.com/2019/01/12/more-lovers-follow-chicken-inn-couple/\">M</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho and Belinda are the couple whose proposal picture at Chicken Inn went viral over December and most of January.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Valentines Day has become heavily commercialised with most partners expecting to be spoilt, Belinda on the contrary said she was not expecting anything from Makho.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I dont expect anything from him really. There are a lot of things that he has to pay for in the future and this is the last thing that Im expecting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, if he wants to do something for me, Ill be glad, said Belinda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":205016} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://nehandaradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Chicken-Inn-couple.jpg\" alt=\"Destiny changer . . . Makhosana Mguni goes down on his knee as he proposes to his sweetheart Belinda Nyoni for a hand in marriage at a Chicken Inn outlet in Bulawayo, on Wednesday last week. The picture has gone viral. Inset: Makhosana and Belinda\" class=\"wp-image-205016\"/><figcaption>Destiny changer . . . Makhosana Mguni goes down on his knee as he proposes to his sweetheart Belinda Nyoni for a hand in marriage at a Chicken Inn outlet in Bulawayo. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For Makhos birthday, Belinda sent him a present.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I understand that he cant be here because of work, but as a way to cheer him up, I sent him a present on Tuesday. It arrived in the afternoon and judging from his reaction, he was happy, said Belinda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho is saving up to pay lobola (bride price) in April this year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thereafter, a wedding date will be set to consolidate their six-year relationship.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like many who are also in long distance relationships, the two will most probably spend their day chatting with each other on WhatsApp.<strong>The Chronicle</strong><ins><br></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'No Valentines for Chicken Inn couple', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'no-valentines-for-chicken-inn-couple', '', '', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=640', 0, 'post', '', 0),
