(642, 2, '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>It is Valentines Day today and lovers worldwide will be showing each other love and affection through heart-adorned cards, bumper boxes of chocolate, bouquets of red roses and teddy bears.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sadly for the Chicken Inn couple  Makhosana Makho Mguni and Belinda Nyoni, they will not be together on this day of love because of distance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho, who celebrated his 28th birthday yesterday, works in South Africa while his fiance Belinda works at a clothing boutique in Bulawayo.<a href=\"https://nehandaradio.com/2019/01/12/more-lovers-follow-chicken-inn-couple/\">M</a></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho and Belinda are the couple whose proposal picture at Chicken Inn went viral over December and most of January.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>As Valentines Day has become heavily commercialised with most partners expecting to be spoilt, Belinda on the contrary said she was not expecting anything from Makho.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I dont expect anything from him really. There are a lot of things that he has to pay for in the future and this is the last thing that Im expecting.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>However, if he wants to do something for me, Ill be glad, said Belinda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":205016} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"https://nehandaradio.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/Chicken-Inn-couple.jpg\" alt=\"Destiny changer . . . Makhosana Mguni goes down on his knee as he proposes to his sweetheart Belinda Nyoni for a hand in marriage at a Chicken Inn outlet in Bulawayo, on Wednesday last week. The picture has gone viral. Inset: Makhosana and Belinda\" class=\"wp-image-205016\"/><figcaption>Destiny changer . . . Makhosana Mguni goes down on his knee as he proposes to his sweetheart Belinda Nyoni for a hand in marriage at a Chicken Inn outlet in Bulawayo. </figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>For Makhos birthday, Belinda sent him a present.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I understand that he cant be here because of work, but as a way to cheer him up, I sent him a present on Tuesday. It arrived in the afternoon and judging from his reaction, he was happy, said Belinda.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Makho is saving up to pay lobola (bride price) in April this year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thereafter, a wedding date will be set to consolidate their six-year relationship.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like many who are also in long distance relationships, the two will most probably spend their day chatting with each other on WhatsApp.<strong>The Chronicle</strong><ins><br></ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'No Valentines for Chicken Inn couple', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '640-revision-v1', '', '', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '2019-02-14 12:06:29', '', 640, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/index.php/2019/02/14/640-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(643, 2, '2019-02-14 12:20:08', '2019-02-14 12:20:08', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Twenty-three illegal miners died on Tuesday evening when interlinked shafts and tunnels at two mines in Battlefields were flooded after the collapse of a dam wall due to heavy rains received in the area.</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The dam wall reportedly collapsed around 11pm on Tuesday night, flooding shafts at the RioZim-owned Cricket Mine and another one owned by a Mr Baxter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The two mines have three linked shafts said to be 30 metres deep with 20 metre-wide tunnels.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There are, however, fears that more miners could have perished in the disaster, while reports also indicated that the water levels in the shafts and tunnels were rising.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mashonaland West provincial administrator Mrs Cecilia Chitiyo yesterday confirmed the incident.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She said the local Civil Protection Unit (CPU) had been activated to offer assistance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are waiting for more information from the people on the ground and the local CPU is on standby to offer assistance as soon as the disaster is confirmed, she said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mrs Chitiyo also travelled to Kadoma last night to meet the local CPU.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We urgently need to mobilise more pumps. As many as we can because the water levels are continuously rising from beneath and we are not sure if the miners had reached an aquifer below, she said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mhondoro-Ngezi district administrator Mrs Fortunate Muzulu, who visited the two mines yesterday afternoon, said chances of rescuing any survivors were very slim.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The names of people believed to have been trapped has reached 23, with 19 reportedly trapped at the RioZim-owned mine with another four from the other mine, she said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Mrs Mazulu said more artisanal miners could have been trapped underground.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The illegal miners, she said, entered the shafts and tunnels under the cover of darkness without the knowledge of mine owners and disappeared early in the morning.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She said rescue operations were also difficult since the shafts were flooded to the surface.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So far, we have been in touch with Zimplats and we are hopeful that they will assist with their bigger pumps to drain the water for us to retrieve the bodies. However, whatever the number of trapped people may be, chances of rescuing any survivors are very slim, she said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>RioZim spokesperson Mr Wilson Gwatiringa, who also visited the site yesterday, confirmed that efforts were underway to drain the water from the shafts.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The shafts where artisanal miners were working last night (Tuesday night) were flooded during the night, trapping them underground. Efforts are underway to pump the water to enable rescue teams to work.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I am not sure how many people are trapped but estimates from their colleagues say above 20.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The operations are led by Ministry of Mines and Mining Development and we are playing a supporting role, he said.&nbsp;<strong>The Herald</strong><ins><br>\n\n</ins></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', '23 miners perish in flooded shafts', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', '23-miners-perish-in-flooded-shafts', '', '', '2019-02-14 12:20:08', '2019-02-14 12:20:08', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=643', 0, 'post', '', 0),
