(659, 2, '2019-02-15 11:49:41', '2019-02-15 11:49:41', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>American based Zimbabwean chimurenga musician, ThomasMapfumo,who recently made headlines after he was reportedly evicted from his lodgings over a $10 000 debt has  approached the High Court in Harare seeking defamation damages from a local journalist accusing the latter of misrepresenting facts on the matter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Popularly known as Mukanya, Mapfumo recently filed a $1 250 000 litigation through his lawyers, Venturas and Samkange and the sued scribe is yet to respond to the litigation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to court papers, Mapfumo said the published article was false and defamatory adding it portrayed him as a musician of no integrity and is dishonest.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The plaintiff (Mapfumo) is an American based Zimbabwean and renowned international musician with a good reputation and impeccable character. He has received numerous recognitions accolades and awards throughout the years for his good work and for being a good representative of Zimbabwe and its citizens. He has thousands if not millions of followers throughout the world, his lawyers said in the lawsuit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The article was false and defamatory. The article shows that the plaintiff is a musician of no integrity and is dishonest. This article was published and read by many people throughout the world with some readers even contacting the plaintiff for verification, clarity and further details.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Defendant (name withheld) published the article without even verifying the accuracy and the truthfulness of the statement with the plaintiff. The statement was designed to humiliate and injure plaintiffs reputation in the eyes of his supporters and the world at large, he said adding he does not owe anyone any amount but rather he is owed by his promoters.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The statement was false and defamatory. Plaintiff does not owe anyone the amount alleged or any amount for that matter, on the contrary, plaintiff is the one owed by the promoters large sums of money. The statement was malicious and baseless. Plaintiff is of good standing in society with good reputation. Plaintiff is therefore entitled to claim damages as set out in the summons.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mapfumo sues journalist over Glen Lorne eviction article', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'mapfumo-sues-journalist-over-glen-lorne-eviction-article', '', '', '2019-02-15 11:49:41', '2019-02-15 11:49:41', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=659', 0, 'post', '', 0),
