(665, 2, '2019-02-15 12:18:52', '2019-02-15 12:18:52', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A local businessman has petitioned the High Court seeking an order to compel controversial politician William Gerald Mutumanje, popularly known as Acie Lumumba to settle US$11 800 being arrears arising from an agreement of sale of a Mercedes Benz Station Wagon ML350 the two parties entered into last year.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>&nbsp;Knoxman Mudariki Moyo filed summons at the High Court and Acie Lumumba is yet to respond to the litigation.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In a plaintiffs declaration which was filed along with the summons, Moyo said he entered into a verbal agreement of sale with Acie Lumumba last year after selling a Mercedes Benz to the latter.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On or about 26 October 2008 the plaintiff (Moyo) entered into a verbal agreement of sale whereby the plaintiff sold a Mercedes Benz Station Wagon ML350 vehicle to the defendant (Mutumanje). In terms of the verbal agreement, the selling price of the Mercedes Benz vehicle was US$50 000, this money was to be settled as follows, defendant was to tender his Range Rover Sport vehicle at a value of US$20 000 to the plaintiff. The remaining balance of US$20 000 (not bond /RTGS) was to be paid to the plaintiff in real united states dollars as cash or paid into the plaintiffs CBZ Nostro account supplied to the defendant, he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>According to the court papers, Moyo said Lumumba retained possession of the vehicle registration book of the Range Rover Sport after delivering it to him (Moyo).</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The plaintiff retained possession of the vehicle registration book of the Mercedes Benz ML 350 as it was a condition of the sale that the book would only be given to defendant upon payment of the full purchase price. The defendant also retained possession of the vehicle registration book of the Range Rover even though this book was supposed to be given to the plaintiff on delivery of the Range Rover motor vehicle as it now belonged to the plaintiff. Defendant was further supposed to sign an affidavit showing that he had sold the Range Rover vehicle to the plaintiff. This was not done, he said.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moyo also said Acie Lumumba managed to pay US$8 200 leaving a balance of US$11 800 which he has neglected or refused to pay despite demand.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Of the remaining balance of US$20 000 the defendant in various factitious instalments has paid the plaintiff a total of US$8 200 leaving a balance of US$11 800. Despite demand and several request, the defendant has failed, neglected or deliberately refused to pay the said amounts due to deliver the registration book of the Range Rover and to attest to an affidavit of sale of the range rover motor vehicle.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The matter is still pending.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Acie Lumumba taken to court over US$11k debt', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'acie-lumumba-taken-to-court-over-us11k-debt', '', '', '2019-02-15 20:27:18', '2019-02-15 20:27:18', '', 0, 'http://www.zimskynews.com/?p=665', 0, 'post', '', 0),
